Stephen Lawrence "Steve" or "Stevie" Winwood (born May 12, 1948 in Handsworth, Birmingham) is an English singer-songwriter and multi-instrumentalist. In addition to his solo career, he was a member of the bands the Spencer Davis Group, Traffic, Go and Blind Faith.

"Dirty City" is a rock song by Steve Winwood from his album Nine Lives, released April 29, 2008.

The song features Eric Clapton on guitar and reached number #1 on Adult Album Alternative radio for 3 weeks.[1]
